ICD-10 entity kind. One of chapter, block, or category. Chapters are top level classification entities. Blocks are high level groupings that do not have a code. Categories are entities that have a code.
ICD-10 depth for kind. For example, a category with kind_depth=2 means it is category whose parent is also a category but grand parent is not.
